<title type="html"><![CDATA[1/23(Sun.-online meeting) How do children choose a best friend?/ How To Never Run Out Of Things To Say In Conversation]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=584&amp;p=607#p607"><![CDATA[
1/23(Sun.-online meeting only) How do children choose a best friend?/ How To Never Run Out Of Things To Say In Conversation. ...(Host: Ellen)<br /><br />加入 Zoom 會議<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ... NKSU5MQT09<br /><br />會議 ID：929 8726 6213<br />密碼：112233<br />--------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:10 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:10-7:40 pm Session 1 Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Presentation 1<br />8:00-8:10 pm Break<br />8:10-8:40: Session 2 Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Presentation 2<br /><br />--------------------------------------------<br /><br />Session 1: How do children choose a best friend?<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.bbc.com/future/article/20211117-how-do-children-choose-a-best-friend">https://www.bbc.com/future/article/2021 ... est-friend</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Q1.Do you think you are the person who is easy to make friends? What kinds of personalities or characteristics do you have? What do your friends think of you? (nice/easy going/stubborn/reliable…)<br /><br />Q2.When you want to choose a friend, what are the elements that you concern? (personal/easy going/the same common…)<br /><br />Q3.Do you still keep in touch with your kindergarten/elementary/college… friends? How do you keep your friendship for so many years? How long do you have a gathering?<br /><br />Q4.Do you agree with the benefits of the article of best friends? What do you learn from your best friend?<br /><br />Q5.If there is the school reunion, will you go? Why or why not? Anything you want to say to your schoolmates/old friends if you meet them?<br /><br />Session 2: How To Never Run Out Of Things To Say In Conversation<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://tw.voicetube.com/videos/61241">https://tw.voicetube.com/videos/61241</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Q1.Are you the person who is shy or open-minded? Do you usually wait for someone to talk with you first or you start a conversation first in a new group?<br /><br />Q2.How do you usually break the ice when you talk to a new friend in a group? What kinds of topics will you start? How do you do for helping new comers to involve more in Royal English club?<br /><br />Q3.Do you have any friend who is very easy to talk with? What personality do they have? Have you ever learned the tips from them? <br /><br />Q4.What are the suitable or forbidden topics in a conversation? Why? If someone always talk about the forbidden topics in the groups, what will you do?<br /><br />Q5.Do you still remember the first time when you speak English in public/on the stage/in Royal English club? How did you feel or overcome the fear? Any tip to share with us?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=46353">Ellen Lu</a> — Tue Jan 11, 2022 9:46 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
